#* {{zh-x|祭 王父 曰 皇祖考，王母 曰 皇祖妣。父 曰 皇考，母 曰 皇妣。夫 曰 皇辟。生 曰 父、曰 母、曰 妻，死 曰 考、曰 妣、曰 嬪。|In sacrificing to them, a grandfather is called 'the [[皇|sovereign]] grand'''father''''; a grandmother, 'the sovereign grandmother'; a father, 'the sovereign '''father''''; a mother, 'the sovereign mother; a husband, 'the sovereign [[辟|pattern]].' While alive, the names of '[[父|father]]', '[[母|mother]]', and '[[妻|wife]]' are used; when they are dead, those of ''''the completed one'''', '[[妣|the corresponding one]]', and '[[嬪|the honored one]]'.|ref=Liji}}

